channel.title: Adding objects
channel.description: I've been adding alot of objects and they all semed to work but when i add this.. c.getPA().checkObjectSpawn(2213, 2845, 3345, 0, 10); //house portal it never seems to show up (objectmanager) any ideas?

item.title: Adding objects
item.dc:creator: @DevinCooley DevinCooley
item.description:
@DevinCooley wrote:

Maybe the coord height level is wrong? try ::tele (your coords here including the third one) and see where you go. If you go where you want the object to be then that just means you have the wrong object id.

item.title: Adding objects
item.dc:creator: @Roar337 Roar337
item.description:
@Roar337 wrote:

you could have wrong coords and if your sure you dont try spawning the object using this command

if (playerCommand.startsWith("object")) { String[] args = playerCommand.split(" "); c.getPA().object(Integer.parseInt(args[1]), c.absX, c.absY, Integer.parseInt(args[2]), 10); }

usually if nothing shows up i figure it dosent exist or dosent have a model
when you use the command it should show up right under you

its ::object id face

if it dosent show up try using a diffrent object id try umm 13405

ofc these are just all guesses but im usually right its worth a try
